[Git Commit Rules]
When generating commit messages (via the sparkle button or chat):

- Use the Conventional Commits standard (feat:, fix:, etc.).
- Use only the summary line (max 50 chars).
- No fluff like "improved styling", "better readability", or "cleaner code".
- Be literal: if height changed, say "change height".
- Format: <type>: <description> (e.g., "style: adjust EventsTable height").
- Never add a body/description unless the diff is massive.

[Nuxt UI]
When working with Nuxt UI components (imports from #ui, @nuxt/ui, or nuxt-ui), use the MCP server user-nuxt-ui: check tool schemas before calling, and prefer its tools for docs, examples, and component usage.
